                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>Vincent had promised to send Theo <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_899">Jules Breton</rs>’s <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_29"><hi rend="italics">Les champs et la mer</hi></ref>; <ref target="let060.xml">see letters 60</ref> and <ref target="let061.xml">61</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_841">Ludwig Uhland</rs> was an important exponent of Late Romanticism in Germany.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>Van Gogh had copied texts, including poems by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_654">Heine</rs> and <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_841">Uhland</rs>, into two little books for Theo. See Pabst 1988, pp. 33-36.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="4" xml:id="note-t-4">
                            

<p>The novel <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_52"><hi rend="italics">L’ami Fritz</hi></ref> by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_591 bio.xml#_594">Erckmann-Chatrian</rs>; <ref target="let055.xml#n-24">see letter 55, n. 24.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="5" xml:id="note-t-5">
                            

<p>The photograph of <rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_1746"><hi rend="italics">The farewells</hi></rs> by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_891">Brion</rs>; <ref target="let054.xml#n-15">see letter 54, n. 15.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="6" xml:id="note-t-6">
                            

<p>It is not know which paintings this refers to.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="7" xml:id="note-t-7">
                            

<p>The painting <rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#noill_74"><hi rend="italics">Ploughing</hi></rs> by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1117">Charles Emile Jacque</rs> had been sent from Goupil’s in Paris, arriving at the Hague branch on 13 September 1875. It was shipped back to Paris on 9 February 1876 (<hi rend="italics">RKD</hi>, <hi rend="italics">Goupil Ledgers</hi>).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
